forgetfulMemoriesCreated.title: Multi-tier architecture pattern: CI enforcement + Local feedback + Background automation
Multi-agent ADR review catches P0 structural violations
Memory-first architecture (ADR-007): Document patterns in memory before code
Thin workflows, testable modules (ADR-006): ALL logic in PowerShell
Role-specific tool allocation (ADR-003): 3-9 curated tools per agent
Exit code 2 signals BLOCKING to Claude across all hooks
Never suppress stderr without capturing for diagnostics
Aggregate jobs must use always() && to prevent enforcement bypass
Error suppression anti-pattern: stderr redirect before LASTEXITCODE
Python 3.13.x SystemError breaks CodeQL - use Python 3.12.8
Verify branch before git operations - SESSION-PROTOCOL mandates
Never use git add -A after failed cherry-pick
SHA-pinning requirement for GitHub Actions prevents supply chain attacks

learnings.content: Bulk import of 435+ learnings requires automated extraction script, not manual processing. Representative sample (14 memories) validates pattern before full automation.
Forgetful auto-linking working excellently - each new memory automatically linked to 3-4 related existing memories at creation time.
Domain-specific projects (16 total) enable targeted semantic retrieval. Project filtering improves query precision.
